(489, 142, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"067bef8\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"75a61b2\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5902ac5\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"6152669\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d075ee0\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost:8080\\/Elementum\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/10\\/elementum10-2.jpg\",\"id\":83}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"}],\"isInner\":true},{\"id\":\"b796031\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"c1a4c12\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-bottom: var(--article-single-p-bottom); color: #000000; font-size: 18px; line-height: var(--article-single-line-height); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bolder;\\\">Kunyu Mountain Shaolin Kung Fu School offers classes taught by full-time professional Wing Chun masters. Learn more about the history and culture from our Wing Chun school below.<\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: var(--article-single-p-bottom); color: #000000; font-size: 18px; line-height: var(--article-single-line-height); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\\\">Wing Chun (also wing tsun or Yong chun in Chinese) kung fu is a splendid Chinese southern internal fist style. There is a saying that there is Tai chi in the north and Wing Chun in the south. Wing Chun has a rich 200 year history, but it is less known than other Kung fu styles. With continuous improvements by descendants and with the development of society, it has become a great historical treasure in the history. Originally, only rich young men could have the chance to learn this martial art, which was called \\u201cShaoye fist\\u201d (shaoye means a son of a rich family). But nowadays, people can learn its practical value, wisdom, and connotation<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":true}],\"isInner\":true}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"7c871e1\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\",\"background_overlay_hover_background\":\"gradient\",\"background_overlay_hover_color_b\":\"#000000\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d49f2f5\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"54bef3f\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-bottom: var(--article-single-p-bottom); color: #000000; font-size: 18px; line-height: var(--article-single-line-height); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\\\">There are many stories about the origin of Yong chun. Among these, the one that it was created by a nun, Wumei, is the most popular. It is said that the southern shaolin temple was burnt by the Qing government in the year of Emperor Kangxi (1654-1722). Five masters (with high kung fu ability) survived that big fire. Of all the masters, Wumei fled to Daliang Mountain, which lies in the border of Sichuan and Yunnan province. The other four masters were Zhisha, Baimei, Feng Daode, and Miaoxia. After arriving at Daling Mountain, Wumei saw a snake and a crane fighting and learned their fighting principles (crane attacks the center and snake moves flexibly). Then she created a new martial art system which was different from her own fist style and changed \\u201cCHANG QIAO DA MA\\u201d (forceful and bold) to \\u201cDUAN QIAO ZHAI MA\\u201d.\\u00a0\\u00a0<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"bcceee2\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"220ce29\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost:8080\\/Elementum\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/10\\/elementum11.jpg\",\"id\":62}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f927a49\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ce17ae6\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"48c6e46\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost:8080\\/Elementum\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/10\\/elementum9-1.jpg\",\"id\":82}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"b03481d\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ac0a112\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-bottom: var(--article-single-p-bottom); color: #000000; font-size: 18px; line-height: var(--article-single-line-height); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );\\\">This martial arts system focuses on borrowing power, defending and attacking at same time, protecting and using your center and winning with smart force. The birth of Wing Chun comes from snake and crane, but it is different from the other animal fist. So, Wing Chun is not purely imitating food-hunting or fighting motions of a single animal, but it comes from the enlightenment of fighting between snake and crane, combining the motions of snake and crane together.Fatefully, Wumei saved Yan Yongchun, who was being forced to marry someone she did not want to. She taught Yongchun her fist form. After that, Yan got married with Liang Bochou, who was from the Jiangxi province and taught Liang this fist form as well.\\u00a0 Learning this fist form helped Liang win against other people for a long time, but he had no idea what the name of this form was. As he learned it from Yan Yongchun, he named it \\u201cYongchun fist\\u201d to show his appreciation. Liang Bochou then passed it to his nephew Liang Langui, who later passed it to the performers of a theatrical troupe named \\u201cFoshan Red Boat\\u201d: Huang Huabao, Liang Erdi, and Lujin. Huang and Liang introduced it to a Foshan person named Liangzan. Lujin passed it to two Foshan people: Feng Shaoqing and Guo Baoquan.<\\/span><\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"372e4ef\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"background_overlay_hover_background\":\"gradient\",\"background_overlay_hover_color_b\":\"#575757\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"b45d145\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"f5f9a7b\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"address\":\"\\u039c\\u03c5\\u03c3\\u03c4\\u03c1\\u03ac 22, \\u0393\\u03bb\\u03c5\\u03c6\\u03ac\\u03b4\\u03b1\",\"zoom\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":16,\"sizes\":[]},\"height\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":315,\"sizes\":[]}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"google_maps\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
